description: Can you corner a bowl? Come learn this and other cool things Tues-Sat at 4:20. There's a lot to stoner culture beyond 'puff puff pass'. See how to be excellent to your fellow smokers! TimeBomb, Bowl Cornering, Weed cleaning, Joint rolling, Edibles.
title: Weed Ettiquette

author: lllama@gmail.com
description: Now that Karen has taught you how to roll beautiful joints, it's time for a practical. Whose reefer will you prefeer?
title: 4.20 Social Hour - A Meeting of the Joint Commitee

author: Technohippy
description: Balefire Temple opens its doors to wise and curious seekers of beauty, truth, peace, and harmony. At this time, we will unveil the pillars of our community as we bring you into our magical realm.
title: Balefire Temple Opening Ceremony

author: emma.grocutt@gmail.com
description: Take your top off and drink wine with us. Because tits and wine are great.
title: Tits & Wine

author: Aury
description: Daily craft cocktail creations, delicious alcohol-free options, and a rotating beer or cider on tap. Music and good company, with vibes ranging from lounging to dance party depending on the day.
title: Happy Hour

author: jessica.spaulding@gmail.com
description: Prepare for your week-long exploration of the Lost Cities and Civilizations. Come get your floaties inspected and registered early for river usage. Be aware that wait times may be longer than usual as we train the new interns at the DFV. We promise to serve long lines, slow service, and drinks.
title: Expedition Launch and DFV Opens!

author: lllama@gmail.com
description: Joints are to getting high as candles are to reading: when normal tools fail completely, they let you get the job done. Karen will help you polish your joint-rolling skills so you're ready for the zombie apocalypse. Papers provided.
title: Essential joint-rolling

author: Ben (There) Tramposh
description: Afternoon workout to power you into indiscretion. Beginning and ending with a cadence run around the perimeter. Rotating instructors lead a flexible workout modifiable for all current energy levels.
title: Remedial PT (Physical Training)

author: amy@snnort.com
description:
Open hosted bar- select from two craft cocktails with a sexy twist. 21+
Each day we feature Plinko! on our Big Board as well as a mystery game with a naughty twist.
title: Afternoon Delight Bar PLUS Dirty Diversions

author: lllama@gmail.com
description: We've got a toaster oven and aren’t afraid to use it! Drop by the Porch daily at 3 pm to enjoy the result of our fearlessness - hot, delicious, fresh-baked cookies.New cookie this year: GF chocolate chip made using dedicated dishes and utensils.
title: Cookie Time!

author: Spidey
description: Compete to win fabulous prizes and Critical "dream vacations." The catch: we can ask questions in the format of *any* popular game show. "Jeopardy" or "Millionaire," "100,000 Pyramid," or "Beat the Clock?" You won't know ...and neither will we!
title: GameShow Game Show

author: mandy.m.bailey@gmail.com
description: Search the 'Lost Cities & Civilizations' of Critical for hidden artifacts and rare relics!
title: HUB Happy Hour - Scavenger Hunt!

author: jberg2@gmail.com
description: Have you ever dreamed of being a space cowboy? How about an android looking for love, or a melodramatic space captain? Then this one-shot RPG is for you! No RPG experience necessary, but costumes strongly encouraged.
title: Lasers & Feelings

author: Redi O'Active
description: Be a hot (semi) nude at Hot Noods.  Learn a few basic burlesque moves and the art of twirling tassels.  Pasties will be provided so space is limited.
title: Tassel Twirling at Hot Noods

author: dmbaker362@gmail.com
description: Come jam out with your clam out at Kamp Kuddle Puddle! Guitars, banjos, hurdy-gurdies, egg shakers, nose whistles, whatever you’ve got is welcome.
title: Acoustic jam

author: morgan@datalinkcontrol.net
description: Come enjoy some champagne/mimosas (and select other beverages) at river's edge. You could go all the way to the finish line, but come be a winner with us instead!
location: On the river behind Seattle Anti-Freeze, just before the floaty finish line.
title: Maggie May's Champagne Lounge

author: Ionan
description: Nothing better on a sweltering summer afternoon than ice-cold Southern sweet tea. Lemon available for those that want it. Don't dawdle, there's only so much to go around... and don't forget your cup.
title: Southern Sweet Iced Tea

author: Ben (There) Tramposh
description: Come reminisce about the good ole days, back when Burning Man was way better. Share a drink and your burning war stories. Your bad decisions inspire us!
title: Pitchers and Bitchers - Spirits and Stories

author: morovius@gmail.com
description:
All sing the praises of the brewing Goddess! At this workshop you'll learn how our ancestors harnessed the magic of fermentation and taste three homebrewed ancient and mystical styles. Bring your cup!
Medieval Gruit
Sumerian Bappir
Butterbeer
title: Siduri's Altar - Ancient Beer Tasting

author: lllama@gmail.com
description: Karen, the official mehendi wali of the Front Porch, will discuss the history of henna and its use in body decoration before teaching you how to apply it in traditional patterns. Small cones of henna will be provided.
title: The History and Art of Henna

author: rangerlooseseal@gmail.com
description: Critical Rangers train annually on consent basics/incidents and response policies for reported sexual assault to promote a safer and more consent-driven event. We again open this training to the public as many have found it valuable. *Developed with generous help from Consent Academy
title: Consent and SART for Rangers (open to the public)

author: Ben (There) Tramposh
description: Open jam session. Some instruments provided, all welcome.
title: Army Band Camp

author: nils@shkoo.com
description: Join us for some strange and sexy iterations of Twister. Will there be floggers? Will there be jello shots? Only god knows what sort of weird stuff is gonna be happening on our beautiful, colorful mat. Win at sports. Make your parents proud.
title: Dirty Twister

author: brieyost@gmail.com
description: FunCon TV's #1 daytime drama: it revolves around the rivalries, romances, and shenanigans of camp dynasties in conflict. Our scripted adventure is your chance to be a soap opera star! Join us on TV or in the studio audience for new twists daily!
title: The Fun and the Restless, Ep. 1

author: Ben (There) Tramposh
description: Come get outfitted and painted in your favorite shades of forest.
title: Tactical Tuesday

author: lllama@gmail.com
description: Learn to make a simple copper ring with a bead. Materials provided.
title: Make your own copper ring

author: Ben (There) Tramposh
description:
Come let our nurses salve your battle scars from the night before. Just tell us where it hurts.
We'll restore you to health, then hand you over to our drill sergeants for more punishment.
title: Sick Call

author: Spidey
description: Your party must manage all their skills and resources *carefully* to beat the Wizard's challenge or die in his dungeon. Succeed and earn a place of honor with the order of The Scarlet Ribbon. A tribute to early modules. Cont WED.
title: Dungeons & Dragons 5e Crit Exclusive - "Just Enough" - 6 pre-gens provided

author: Ben (There) Tramposh
description: Morning workout to sweat out last night's bad decisions and prepare for badder days ahead. Rotating instructors lead you through their own unique exercise technique.
title: Morning PT (Physical Training)

author: amandadneedham@gmail.com
description: Back by popular demand. Find your life changing toasted burrito experience prominently displayed on the Esplanade at the concrete pad. Listen for the dinner bell.
title: Breakfast Burritos

author: beaverlakestables@gmail.com
description: We're trashy and bacon goes fast, so hustle up!
title: Morning Coffee and Bacon in the Trailer Park

author: madame.heather@gmail.com
description: Enjoy a tranquil moment before the morning train runs through Critical, by joining us in an unrepeatable moment in time, while taking part in the traditional chanoyu ceremony. Each day will feature a unique seasonal variation - not to be repeated.
title: Experience Ichi-go ichi-e

author: Technohippy
description: Meet the Balefire Community! Please bring food and drink to share.
title: Balefire Community Potluck

author: Spidey
description: The Starlite Lounge opens for early arrivers who need a space to chillax after a hard day of camp construction. Luxuriate on our rugs and cushions whilst we pour the shots and Ella sings in the background. Experience the Lounge before the crowds. 21+
title: Late-Nite Loungin' for Early Arrivals

author: Spidey
description: Queer and Arriving Early? Come to our Queerly Bird mixer and maybe find a "buddy" to pace you for the week! We can't promise you'll find Mr (or Ms) Right, but you might just find "Mr Right Now," and isn't that enough? Drinks and snacks served. 21+
title: "Queerly Bird Gets the Wyrm" Mixer

author: morgan@datalinkcontrol.net
description: The legendarry La Toro Quesadilla Cart will be serving up hot goodness to all the denizens and travelers of the lost cities.
location: Follow the smell, look for fire (and a line), likely near Seattle Anti-Freeze.
title: Toro Quesadillas

author: The One and Only Chloe
description: Come play bingo to learn some sexy lingo!
title: Sexy Lingo Bingo

author: thenora@gmail.com
description: Join friends you haven’t met yet to choose your own adventure in temporary micro community. Don a blindfold and let our guide help you discover sensory artifacts and explore perceptions and stories. A new adventure starts every hour. Come alone?
title: Burn in the Dark

author: luckybob10@gmail.com
description: Stop by and say, "Fuck You Wizards!" Be the first to try out our new attractions. Get a sneak preview of our wizardly potions and elixirs. Relax on the Magic Carpet.
title: Fuck You I'm A Wizard - Monday

author: Spidey
description: Take a flop down the river and hope to survive a turn in fortune at our 2019 Hold 'Em tournament. Highest chip count wins a coveted Starlite shot glass and bragging rights! Vegas-style service to players. 21+
title: Starlite Hold 'Em Poker Tournament

author: brieyost@gmail.com
description: Tune in nightly for comprehensive coverage of nipple sightings, inter-camp political turmoil, troubling reports of Sparkle Ponies by the river, and whatever else the anchor deems worthy of broadcast.
title: FunCon TV Nightly News

author: info@hipspro.com
description: Come join us and refresh your cells with a steaming bowl of nourishing soup. After a day of play, sit and relax with us and get refreshed. Be ready for a night of partying with some vegetables in you. We will be alternating soups daily, so check our A board to see what is on the menu of the day.
title: Woodstock Soup Kitchen

author: brieyost@gmail.com
description: Funintended Consequences' famous lounge. Shmooze with the stars of FunCon TV, prepare for your own moment on screen, or just grab a drink from the bar and relax. Come by nightly midnight to 2am for our special Late Nite Lounge.
title: The Green Room

author: lllama@gmail.com
description: Come share a bowl and chill on the porch as we watch the parade of lovely Criticalians pass by. Bring your best bud or get acquainted with ours.
title: 4.20 Social, Flower Power Hour edition

description: We've got a toaster oven and aren’t afraid to use it! Drop by the Porch daily at 3 pm to enjoy the result of our fearlessness - hot, delicious, fresh-baked cookies.New cookie this year: GF chocolate chip made using dedicated dishes and utensils.

author: amandadneedham@gmail.com
description: For those early intrepid explorers exhausted from a days labor setting up camp, let us bring you ours d’evours. The cream of the crop from the top of the bottom of the barrel. An oral exploration unlike any other. Listen for the dinner bell.
title: Ours D’evours

author: mandy.m.bailey@gmail.com
description:
Chill out with other introverts, and do a little crafting and chatting!
We will have markers and supplies for creating mini works of art to keep, or share. Strike up a conversation with a new friend, in a safe environment.
(No personal interaction required.)
title: HUB Happy Hour - Introverts Anonymous, Crafts N' Chats

author: agodwin89@gmail.com
description:
Sweet Pea,
Those wild squirrels had a party in my flowerbed again! The petal carnage! Grandma would love it if you and all your buds came to paint a wooden flower. If you want to stick it in my garden you can, or take it home.

Love you bunches,
Grandma
title: Painting Flowers

description: There are rumors of a lost treasure waiting to be found. Will you be the one to find it? There are clues scattered around the area that show the way... if you can decipher them. Our camp is with the modern day Hotlanteans- come join our expedition!
title: Seek the lost treasure of Hotlantis!

author: jtranchida@gmail.com
description: Long ago, a magical artifact was buried deep beneath the streets of Seattle. It sat dormant for centuries until struck by Bertha the mechanical mole, shattering into the Amulets of Rune. Pick up an amulet at the Pagoda of Rule to begin your quest.
title: The Amulets of Rune

author: Ben (There) Tramposh
description: Come play doctor, nurse, or wounded soldier at the BDBC Aid Station

description: Stop by CM to become an official mail carrier. Grab any available mail, roam the grounds trying to find the location. Deliver mail. Meet new friends. Bask in the love of recipients. Get Swag. M-F 11am to 4pm.

description: Sugar Pie, The wolves blew the house down, Deloris is gone and I’m worried about you. Come by anytime and see my flowers. I don’t know about this lost civilization thing, but I’m sure glad to see some bees. Love, Grandma
